data.name: adidas Stan Smith Peter Pan (Kids)
data.story: Offered in grade school sizing, the Disney x adidas Stan Smith J ‘Peter Pan & Tinkerbell’ spotlights a pair of iconic characters from the Disney pantheon. The vegan-friendly upper, made with 50% recycled content, features a white synthetic leather base with unique branding elements. ‘Peter Pan’ is imprinted on the latera quarter panel of the right shoe, while the character himself appears on the tongue tag. The left shoe features Tinkerbell’s name and likeness in the same areas. Satin heel tabs are marked with the phrase ‘It’s Not Easy Being Green’ across both shoes. data.name: adidas NMD R1 V2 Damian Lillard (GS)
data.story: Offered in kids sizing, the debut of the Damian Lillard x adidas NMD_R1 V2 J ‘D.O.L.L.A.’ coincides with the launch of the NBA star’s fourth studio album, ‘Different on Levels the Lord Allowed.’ The lifestyle runner features a black knit upper with special branding elements drawn from the athlete’s rap persona, including a barcode graphic on the medial quarter panel and Dame D.O.L.L.A.’s personal logo on the tongue. Printed across the sneaker’s lateral side are lyrics from the Dame’s protest song, ‘Blacklist’: ‘We just strivin’ for equality/Acknowledge me.’ Contrasting pink accents settle on the heel strap, posterior NMD plug and rubber outsole. A full-length Boost midsole returns energy with every step.

data.story: The adidas 4DFWD Pulse J ‘Black Signal Green’ brings the brand’s cutting-edge 4D cushioning technology to a performance running shoe built for kids. The breathable Primegreen upper is made with 50% recycled content and pairs open black mesh with a neon green textile underlay. The latter hue is repeated on floating three-stripes coated in a reflective finish. A 3D-printed heel cradle is incorporated into the foam midsole, yielding an effortless stride by absorbing impact and redirecting the energy forward. Underfoot, a high-traction rubber outsole delivers superior grip.

The 3D-printed lattice structure is precisely angled under the heel, allowing it to redirect the force of impact into forward motion with each stride. The upshot: a smoother and less taxing running experience.

data.story: The June 2019 release of the adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Kids 'Antlia Non-Reflective' sees the design in a pale yellow-green hue. Reflective and non-reflective versions of the 'Antlia' were released exclusively in Europe. This kids' sized shoe stays close to the design of 2016's 350 V2, with a flexible Primeknit upper and semi-translucent window, but drops the typical heel tab. Every step is cushioned with full-length Boost cushioning within a TPU cage for a responsive feel, finished off with rubber tread.

data.name: adidas Ultra Boost 2019 Toy Story Buzz Lightyear (Youth)
data.story: The June 2019 UltraBoost 19 Kids 'Buzz Lightyear' collaboration with Toy Story and adidas takes kids 'To infinity and beyond.' Sporting a lightweight and breathable Primeknit upper, the sneaker helps keep growing feet comfortable. Solar Red and Solar Yellow are reminiscent of Buzz Lightyear's spacesuit, while purple designs at the heel counter depict the same hue of the toy hero's wings. Graphics on the insole and Pixar branding on the tongue and heel tab add contrast to the silhouette.

data.name: adidas Ultra Boost 2019 Toy Story 4 Woody (Youth)
data.story: adidas brings back 90s childhood memories with the Toy Story 4 x UltraBoost 19 J 'Toy Story 4' sneaker. This May 2019 release is outfitted with a Primeknit upper and Three-Stripes lacing overlays that represent Woody’s outfit. The blue heel cage and gum rubber sole is a nod to the protagonist’s signature denim jeans and cowboy boots. The beloved animated icon can be found on the insole of the kids’-sized sneaker.

data.name: adidas Continental 80 Toy Story 4 Forky (Youth)
data.story: To celebrate the fourth installment of the beloved Toy Story franchise, the Three-Stripes brand and Disney teamed up to drop remixed kids’ versions of some of adidas’ most popular models for a June 2019 release. Blending 80s style with modern design, the Toy Story 4 x Continental 80 Kids 'Forky' leather sneaker sports retro-style, two-toned trimmings, accented with the gang's newcomer, Forky, on the heel and sockliner.

data.name: adidas NMD R1 Toy Story 4 Bo Peep (Youth)
data.story: adidas and Disney, powerhouses in their own fields, combined forces to revamp kids’-sized versions of some the Three-Stripes brand’s top models inspired from Pixar’s popular Toy Story film series. Dropped in June 2019, the Toy Story 4 x NMD_R1 Kids 'Bo Peep' sneaker is dressed in a pastel-colored stretch knit upper, detailed with a Bo Peep sockliner, as well as a polka dot Boost sole with the character’s name.

data.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Black (Kids) (Non-Reflective)
data.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Kids 'Black Non-Reflective' shoe casts the coveted sneaker in youth sizing for its June 2019 release. This non-reflective edition reprises many features from 2016's original 350 V2, including a flexible Primeknit upper with a translucent lateral stripe, heel loop and integrated lacing to personalize the fit. For a responsive feel below, adidas' revolutionary Boost cushioning takes position within a translucent TPU shell.

adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Glow (Kids)
data.story: Issued in May 2019, the adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 GID Kids 'Glow' sneaker remixes the unconventional icon with updated functionality. The Primeknit bootie illuminates in the dark as a result of a fluorescent green treatment. Rope laces, a signature heel pull and a translucent monofilament stripe on the lateral side give the shoe its distinctive look. Encased in a Tubular rubber sole, Boost technology helps improve energy return.

data.name: adidas Harden Vol. 3 Marvel Iron Man (Youth)
data.story: The Marvel x adidas Harden Vol. 3 J sneaker from the 'Heroes Among Us' collection was released with the premiere of Avengers: Endgame in April 2019. This kid's version represents Iron Man's iconic battle suit in molded synthetic textile accented by golden Three-Stripes and a debossed Stark Industries logo on heel. The superhero's helmet embellishes the tongue. A cushioned midsole and icy translucent rubber outsole round up the look.

data.name: adidas Pro Vision Marvel Captain Marvel (Youth)
data.story: adidas recruited some of the NBA and WNBA’s top athletes to join forces with MCU heroes for the April 2019 Heroes Among Us collection in conjunction with the premiere of Avengers: Endgame. The Candace Parker Marvel x Pro Vision J ‘Captain Marvel' sneaker remodels the adult version for kids’ feet. The textile upper, ripstop midfoot cage and Bounce cushioning provide superior support, wrapped up in the celestial warrior’s color palette.

data.name: adidas Dame 5 Marvel Black Panther (Youth)
data.story: Made for big kids, the Marvel Avengers x adidas Dame 5 J ‘Heroes Among Us: Black Panther’ launched in 2019 as part of a collaborative five-piece pack celebrating the premier of ‘Avengers: Endgame.’ Damian Lillard’s fifth signature shoe draws inspiration from the Black Panther, featuring black and purple tones on a patterned textile upper. Unique details include a Black Panther badge on the left tongue and ‘Wakanda Forever’ printed across both heel tabs.

data.name: adidas NMD R1 Japan Pack White 2019 (Youth)
data.story: Since its debut in 2015, the NMD has remained a staple of the adidas Originals line, sporting a street-ready style that blends technical materials with modern comfort. The NMD_R1 J 'Japan Colorblock' sneaker is a kids’ version of the adult silhouette that released as part of the ‘Japan’ April 2019 series. It sports a knit textile upper in Cloud White with contrasting Three-Stripes branding and Japanese character embellishments throughout. Protective Lush Blue and red taping dresses the rear midsole plug and heel counter, while a Boost midsole provides responsive cushioning underfoot.

The distinctive netting is echoed on the lightweight EVA midsole. A rubber outsole with a diverse tread pattern hits the pavement below.

data.name: adidas Prophere Trace Pink (Youth)
data.story: In 2018, the trend of chunky sneakers reached new heights. To match this demand without compromising its history of athletic performance, adidas released the Prophere. The lightweight runner features a knit upper with a flexible elastic collar, while the sculpted sidewalls of its EVA midsole result in an on-trend oversized profile. The Three Stripes are formed by a trio of synthetic suede overlays in ‘Trace Pink’, a colorway exclusively available in kids sizes.

data.name: adidas Prophere Raw Grey (Youth)
data.story: With high, sculpted sidewalls and thick synthetic suede overlays doubling as the Three Stripes, the Prophere is a runner that also sticks to the 2018 trend for chunky silhouettes. Despite its bold profile, the flexible stretch-knit upper, elastic collar and cushioned midsole ensure its status as a performance sneaker. The ‘Raw Grey’ colorway is a kid-size edition of the Prophere.

Outfitted in signature Primeknit, this 'Shock Yellow' sneaker's upper wicks away moisture while offering a breathable, supportive fit. The Fitcounter heel optimizes Achilles movement, while Boost cushioning provides a responsive ride. Underfoot, a Stretchweb outsole and Continental Rubber deliver natural flex and excellent traction.

data.name: adidas Ultra Boost 4.0 Parley White Blue (Youth)

A material made by converting plastic water bottles into the knit seen throughout the upper. This fabric features a unique gradient that consists of light blue and teal accents throughout, while the white Boost midsole ensures premium and responsive comfort.

Part of a two-colorway pack of adidas UltraBoost 4.0 sneakers released in August 2018, this version of the UltraBoost 4.0 'Show Your Stripes' sneaker comes dressed in Core Black on a stretchy Primeknit upper that shows off its Cloud White branded TPU midfoot cage. Underfoot, a textured midsole equipped with responsive Boost cushioning is offset by a black rubber outsole.

data.name: adidas Ultra Boost 4.0 Dark Mocha (Youth)
data.story: Released in November of 2017, the adidas ‘Mocha’ colorway was the fourth installment of the UltraBoost 4.0 collection. This kids' version covers the sneaker’s lightweight flexible Primeknit upper in shades of Core Black and Raw Gold. The Three-Stripes lacing cage at the midfoot provides an adapted fit for optimal support. The midsole is reinforced with adidas’ trademark Boost energy-returning technology, perfect for long-distance running.

data.name: adidas Tennis HU Pharrell Williams Tactile Rose (GS)
data.story: Inspired by the 1970s classic, the Stan Smith, acclaimed entertainment visionary Pharrell Williams collaborated with the adidas team for the Pharrell x Tennis Hu J sneaker, released in August 2017. This kids' version celebrates the ‘Hues of Humanity,’ emphasized with the artist's Equality logo patch on heel. The breathable mesh upper and lining is supported by a rubber outsole, textured with a matching mesh-like finish.

data.name: adidas Ultra Boost 3.0 Multi-Color (Youth)
data.story: adidas released the Ultra Boost J 3.0 'Multi-Color' in July 2017. This grade school version of the performance running shoe takes on multiple bright colors throughout the Primeknit upper, featuring a black base that makes the rainbow hues especially stand out. Additional hits of black cover the lining, laces and TPU midfoot cage. The shoe’s embossed Ultra Boost branding is finished in tonal fashion, giving the heel counter a blacked-out look. A full-length Boost midsole in white contrasts the black Continental Rubber outsole underfoot.

data.name: adidas Harden Vol. 1 LS Night Life (Youth)
data.story: Built with adidas’ performance basketball componentry, the Harden Vol. 1 LS Primeknit ‘Night Life’ is equipped with a lifestyle twist, featuring a Primeknit application throughout the upper. The reformed off-court look is complemented with a full-length Boost midsole, while the tongue logo is given an iridescent finish.

data.name: adidas Ultra Boost 3.0 Parley Coral Bleaching (Youth)
data.story: The partnership between adidas and Parley involves using plastic bottles to built the knit on Ultra Boosts. In keeping with their conservation theme, the ‘Icey Blue’ was created to increase awareness of coral bleaching. Along with an Icey Blue Primeknit upper created from recycled material, each shoe comes equipped with an NFC chip that allows the wearer to learn more about Parley’s objective to protect the ocean.

data.name: adidas Ultra Boost Uncaged Solid Grey Multi-Color (Youth)
data.story: Modeled after the adult-sized version, the UltraBoost Uncaged J 'Multi-Color sneaker is constructed with scaled-down design. Dropped in January 2017, the kids' shoe consists of a stretch knit textile that wraps the upper for a sock-like fit. This rendition ditches the Three-Stripes cage for unrestricted movement. A molded Fitcounter heel provides enhanced stability while the sneaker sits atop responsive Boost cushioning.

data.name: adidas Superstar White Iridescent Zebra (Youth)
data.story: Drawing inspiration from the 60s and 70s adidas icon, the Superstar J continues the original’s legacy for the next generation, blending old-school style with scaled-down, kid-friendly design. The shoe is constructed with a leather upper decorated with a multicolored, zebra-print Three-Stripes and heel overlay. The foot is protected with by its signature rubber reinforced toe. Plush foam and a durable outsole ride below.

data.name: adidas EQT Support Adv Triple Black (Youth)
data.story: The adidas EQT Support ADV J sneaker is defined by futuristic elements in this 90s era classic from January 2017. A predominantly Core Black color scheme is interwoven with gray fibers in an ikat pattern throughout the Primeknit upper. The iconic Three-Stripes motif is expressed by lateral straps and tonal midfoot reliefs. A curvy TPU cage wraps around the heel and across the quarter panel. Underfoot, the rubber outsole features dual traction for better grip.

adidas NMD XR1 Glitch Camo (Youth)

It also comes with a black leather heel patch, a Semi Solar red heel tab, white Boost midsole, and white and red outsole. This listing is for youth sizes.

data.name: adidas NMD R1 Core Black (Youth)
data.story: On October 1, 2016, adidas released a kids’ version of the NMD R1 ‘Core Black’ seven months after the adult version hit the market. The NMD R1 ‘Core Black’ is a variation on the original from 2015, the only difference being the black and white EVA plugs.

data.name: adidas NMD R1 Champs Burgundy Grey (Youth)

Released in August 2016, this kid's sized sneaker was a Champs Sports exclusive

data.name: adidas Ultra Boost 2.0 Silver Medal (Youth)
data.story: This grade school edition of the adidas Ultra Boost 2.0 'Silver Medal' released August 2016 as part of an ‘Olympic Medal’ pack. Like its Gold and Bronze Ultra Boost counterparts, this colorway features a Primeknit upper mounted atop a white Boost midsole.The Primeknit construction features a gradient effect on the vamp, introduced with the Ultra Boost 2.0, rendered here in black and grey shades. The heel counter, finished in metallic silver, gives the nod to the 2nd place medal.

data.name: adidas Ultra Boost 3.0 Triple White (Youth)
data.story: This grade school version of the adidas Ultra Boost 3.0 'Triple White' released in December 2016, featuring a monochromatic design that showcases the running shoe’s performance features. They include the signature Primeknit upper, articulated in a rib-like knit, along with a partially translucent midfoot cage and solid white heel counter. More white is found on the Boost midsole and the Continental Rubber Stretchweb outsole underfoot.

data.name: adidas Ultra Boost Uncaged Core Black (Youth)
data.story: Released in June 2016, the adidas Ultra Boost Uncaged J 'Core Black' is a junior-sized colorway that combines a black and grey speckled Primeknit upper with a black sock-like collar, black heel counter, white Boost midsole, and black Continental rubber outsole.

data.name: adidas Ultra Boost Uncaged Ray Red (Youth)
data.story: This grade school edition of the adidas Ultra Boost Uncaged combines the sock-like fit of the Primeknit upper, finished in a blend of Shock Red, Ray Red and Ray Pink, with the responsive cushioning of a full-length Boost midsole. adidas’ Torsion System in the midfoot works with the former to support the foot’s natural movement, while the Stretchweb rubber outsole supports the latter with traction in all directions.

data.name: adidas NMD R1 Bright Cyan (Youth)
data.story: On June 26, 2016, adidas released a kids version of its NMD R1 ‘Bright Cyan’ sneaker. It’s a predominantly white shoe with a pop of Cyan (pronounced like ‘Scion’) in the EV plug. Although the shoe may be for smaller feet, it still boasts all the classic NMD features including Boost technology, a Primeknit upper, and a three-stripes logo made with reflective 3M technology.

data.name: adidas NMD R1 Unity Pink (Youth)
data.story: This striking pink youth NMD_R1 J colorway combines a raspberry mesh upper with blue welded Three-Stripes, pink TPU eyestays, a blue TPU heel patch, and pink signature NMD heel tabs. The bold upper is contrasted with a white Boost midsole featuring tonal EVA inserts, and a crisp white rubber outsole.

data.name: adidas NMD R1 Solid Grey (Youth)
data.story: The adidas NMD R1 ‘J’ is a sneaker made exclusively in kids sizes. Although the shoe may be for smaller feet, it still boasts all the classic NMD features, including Boost technology, a Primeknit upper, and a three-stripes logo made with reflective 3M technology. The shoe is a grey-dominated colorway with 'The Brand With The 3 Stripes' written on its heel tag.

data.name: adidas Ultra Boost 2.0 Triple White (Youth)
data.story: Released in May 2016, this Ultra Boost 2.0 J 'Triple White' upgrades the Ultra Boost 1.0 'White' by ditching the mesh collar for Primeknit and the black outsole for white Continental rubber. This listing is for kid's sizes.

data.name: adidas Ultra Boost Deep Sea (Youth)
data.story: The women's-exclusive adidas UltraBoost 2.0 'Deep Sea' first was added to the UltraBoost family in 2016. This shoe features a Primeknit upper that shifts in tone from the toe box to the rear. Bright blue laces hold the footcage in place for stability and lockdown. This release features a black heel guard, white Boost midsole and a black Continental rubber outsole.

data.name: adidas Ultra Boost 2.0 Core Black Solar Red (Youth)
data.story: Released in June 2016, the adidas Ultra Boost 2.0 J 'Solar Red' combines a red and black gradient Primeknit upper with a matte black cage, orange laces, white Boost midsole, and Solar Red outsole. This listing is for kid's sizes only.

data.name: adidas NMD R1 Light Onyx (Youth)
data.story: The adidas NMD emerges with a primarily grey hue throughout the upper’s mesh and neoprene construction, which forms a sock-like fit. The white Boost midsole is designed for comfort and energy return, while the grey and red midsole TPU plugs reinforce overall support as well as add a pop of color. adidas branding appears on the red bumper, while the trefoil logo appears in white on the heel.

data.name: adidas NMD R1 Shadow Blue (Youth)
data.story: Inspired by a number of classic adidas models like the Micro Pacer and Rising Star, the NMD Runner merges time-tested functionality and contemporary design. This junior version brings together Shadow Blue and white on its textile upper, energy-returning Boost midsole, and leather heel badge. Solid Magenta accents arrive on the laces and branded EVA midsole plugs.

data.name: adidas NMD R1 Core Black Mesh (Youth)
data.story: This NMD Runner J 'Tokyo' dropped in a St. Patrick’s Day ‘City Pack’ in 2016. It sports a sock-like black mesh upper, fused black 3-Stripe branding, and a white TPU heel patch. The midsole features a white Boost unit, blue adidas branded accents, and a black EVA midsole bumper. A black and blue outsole rounds out the understated look. This listing is for youth sizes.

data.name: adidas Superstar White Iridescent (Youth)
data.story: The Superstar J 'Iridescent' delivers a vibrant pop of color to the classic adidas silhouette, offered in kids’ sizing. The model’s signature details remain intact, including a white leather upper, rubber shell toe and gold foil ‘Superstar’ branding on the quarter panel. This shoe’s defining characteristic arrives via the Three-Stripes and heel tab, which are rendered with a unique iridescent finish incorporating a blend of blue and pink hues. A durable rubber cupsole sports a herringbone pattern on the outsole.

data.name: adidas Ultra Boost 3.0 Noble Red (Youth)
data.story: The kids’-sized adidas UltraBoost 3.0 J 'Noble Red' starts with an all-Primeknit multicolored upper based in a red, black and green, and a sturdy footcage lacing system that doubles as the brand’s famous Three-Stripes. A heel guard, tongue patch and extended collar come in a monochrome tone for contrast, and it all sits atop the responsive cushioning of the Boost midsole and Continental rubber outsole.

data.name: adidas Originals Teyana Taylor Harlem GLC (Youth)
data.story: G.O.O.D. Music artist Teyana Taylor partnered with adidas Originals in 2013 for the Teyana Taylor X GLC Promo ‘Harlem.’ Pairing Taylor’s streetwear style with luxe materials, the unique look features a scaly, bronze premium Italian leather upper with an oversized Three-Stripes cage and trefoil logos on the tongue and ankle. A rubber-wrapped wire rib cage is featured at the heel, with a black sole unit underfoot. The sneaker was launched by Teyana Taylor, Big Sean and Pusha T at an in-store event in Houston during the 2013 NBA All-Star weekend.

data.story: When designer Horst Dassler created the adidas Superstar in 1969, he intended it as a hoops shoe, but by the 80s the silhouette had abandoned courtwear for streetwear, thanks to the popularity of its now-iconic rubber shell toe. The adidas Superstar Foundation J keeps the heritage going, in a white leather upper with the Three-Stripes in pink and a heel overlay with a trefoil logo. The midsole also follows the traditional line, in white rubber, along with the herringbone outsole.
